snippet.textDisplay: Sir, I understand and share your love for traditional music and I utmost respect it. But, u can't Know music if u talk about drawing a line when creating music. If our ancestors had 'drawn a line' at what was considered music and what was considered "rape of music" the ENTIRE world would be listening to the clanking of rocks and banging of hands today. CokeStudio is a platform where people who enjoy WorldMusic come together through blending of different genres. Loosen up, n let the music play! .

snippet.textDisplay: My dear friend, I know music pretty well, and not just the kind belonging to my state or my country or my culture, and I always accept music the way it is. But then, sometimes, as is the case here, people don't know where to draw the line, and allow their enthusiasm to get the better of themselves and ruin something that was just pristine. Let us leave a few things as God meant them to be .. including nature :) Rajasthani, Avadhi & Baul music can rarely be improvised upon as 'REMIXES' ! Period.
